[{"id":"VR854873","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two mirrors labeled Mirror 1 and Mirror 2. Mirror 1 is horizontal, and its right edge intersects Mirror 2. Mirror 2 is slanted upwards to the right making an angle of 110 degrees with Mirror 1. A ray is shown coming from the left and slants downward to the right striking Mirror 1 at its midpoint. The ray makes an angle of 50 degrees with a perpendicular dash line to Mirror 1. \" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR854873.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two flat mirrors, Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, are joined together and meet at an angle of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"110 degrees\"><math alttext=\"110 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msup><mn>110</mn><mo>∘</mo></msup></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. A laser beam is incident on Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> at an angle of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"50 degrees\"><math alttext=\"50 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msup><mn>50</mn><mo>∘</mo></msup></math></span></span> from the normal. The beam is reflected from Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and is then incident on Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, where it is reflected a second time. What is the angle between the final reflected beam and the normal to Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR854873_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"30 degrees\"><math alttext=\"30 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msup><mn>30</mn><mo>∘</mo></msup></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"40 degrees\"><math alttext=\"40 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msup><mn>40</mn><mo>∘</mo></msup></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"50 degrees\"><math alttext=\"50 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msup><mn>50</mn><mo>∘</mo></msup></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"60 degrees\"><math alttext=\"60 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msup><mn>60</mn><mo>∘</mo></msup></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":3}]